ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The above newswire (and others currently available on the web) do not give
specifics on the clinical presentation of this current suspected cases of
SARS, nor does it mention the specific tests used to make the diagnosis of
SARS other than to mention WHO approved tests were used. At present there
is no official information available on either the Singapore Ministry of
Health or the WHO SARS website to clarify if the case matches the
pre-established case definition for SARS. Given the extensive experience
of the Singaporean health sector with SARS during the outbreak earlier this
year, the above taken measures described in these newswires seem highly
appropriate pending further information on this case. Until more
information is received, this report/posting is most appropriately titled
"suspected" with a request for more information from authoritative sources.
- Mod.MPP]
